Defendant Jordan L. Henke in court.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea agreement put into the record. Victim is in the courtroom.  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Court finds defendant freely and voluntarily waives right to an attorney.  Attorney Tlusty amends 16CM42 to Misd. Disorderly Conduct - 947.01.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to the amended charge.   Plea colloquy.  Plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently; factual basis exists.  Court finds defendant guilty of DC - 947.01.  Court dismisses and read in Case No. 16CM50.   In 16CM42 the court orders court costs; DNA sample and surcharge; letter of apology to the victim due within one week of plea and sentencing and preapproved by victim witness coordinator.  The costs are to be paid at the rate of $25.00 a month beginning August 12, 2016. Appeal rights given to defendant.   - rt
